  "texts": [
    "Below, we explain the relation between these two types of hypergraphs and the construction process.A hyperedge can be used to represent two types of multiway relationships: In a document hypergraph, a hyperedge (connecting document nodes) can be constructed between documents that mention the same keyword.",
    "In this case, the hyperedge represents the co-mention of a keyword.",
    "In a keyword hypergraph, a hyperedge (connecting keyword nodes) can be constructed between keywords if they are mentioned together in the same document.",
    "In this case, the hyperedge represents a co-occurrence relationship between keywords.",
    "In other words, the two hypergraphs are built from the same corpus, using the same relationship information, but from different perspectives."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}